msgid ""
"To select the Theme you want to play, go to the Theme section. The Theme is "
"loaded by clicking on &nbsp;<guibutton>OK</guibutton> or <guibutton>Apply</"
"guibutton>. The current game will be ended and a new one started. You can "
"click on the &nbsp;<guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button to restore the "
"default Theme."
msgstr ""
"Para escoller o tema co que se quere xogar hai que ir á sección Tema. O tema "
"cárgase premendo o botón <guibutton>Aceptar</guibutton> ou "
"<guibutton>Aplicar</guibutton>. O xogo actual remata e comeza un novo. "
"Pódese premer o botón <guibutton>Predeterminado</guibutton> para restaurar o "
"tema predeterminado."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "Arena"
msgstr "Escenario"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To select the Arena you want to play, go to the Arena section. The Arena "
#| "is loaded by clicking on <guibutton>OK</guibutton> or <guibutton>Apply</"
#| "guibutton>. The current game will be ended and a new one started. You can "
#| "click on the <guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button to restore the "
#| "default Arena."
msgid ""
"To select the Arena you want to play, go to the Arena section. The Arena is "
"loaded by clicking on &nbsp;<guibutton>OK</guibutton> or <guibutton>Apply</"
"guibutton>. The current game will be ended and a new one started. You can "
"click on the &nbsp;<guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button to restore the "
"default Arena."
msgstr ""
"Para escoller o escenario co que se quere xogar hai que ir á sección "
"Escenario. O escenario cárgase premendo o botón <guibutton>Aceptar</"
"guibutton> ou <guibutton>Aplicar</guibutton>. O xogo actual remata e comeza "
"un novo. Pódese premer o botón <guibutton>Predeterminado</guibutton> para "
"restaurar o escenario predeterminado."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:330
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have self-made <application>Clanbomber</application> arenas, you "
#| "can import them by clicking on <guibutton>Import Clanbomber Arenas</"
#| "guibutton>. &granatier; is looking in <filename class=\"directory\">~/."
#| "clanbomber/maps</filename> for the arenas. The default "
#| "<application>Clanbomber</application> arenas are already shipped with "
#| "&granatier;."
msgid ""
"If you have self-made <application>Clanbomber</application> arenas, you can "
"copy them to <filename class=\"directory\">~/.clanbomber/maps</filename>, "
"where &granatier; will look for them. The default <application>Clanbomber</"
"application> arenas are already shipped with &granatier;."
msgstr ""
"Se dispós de escenarios do <application>Clanbomber</application> feitos por "
"ti mesmo, pódelos importar premendo <guibutton>Importar escenarios do "
"Clanbomber</guibutton>. &granatier; busca os escenarios en <filename class="
"\"directory\">~/.clanbomber/maps</filename>. Os escenarios predeterminados "
"do <application>Clanbomber</application> xa se inclúen con &granatier;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you select <guibutton>Random Mode</guibutton>, a random arena will be "
"used for each new round. If there are arenas you don't want to play, you can "
"uncheck them."
msgstr ""
"Se escolles <guibutton>Modo aleatorio</guibutton> úsase un escenario ao chou "
"para cada rolda. De haber escenarios nos que non queiras xogar, desmárcaos."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Player"
msgstr "Xogador"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:361
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To select the Player you want to play, go to the Player section and "
#| "select the Players with the checkboxes. The Shortcuts can be changed by "
#| "clicking on the button for the action you want to change and then "
#| "pressing the key you want to use. The changes are loaded by clicking on "
#| "<guibutton>OK</guibutton> or <guibutton>Apply</guibutton>. The current "
#| "game will be ended and a new one started. You can click on the "
#| "<guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button to restore the default Shortcuts."
msgid ""
"To select the Player you want to play, go to the Player section and select "
"the Players with the checkboxes. The Shortcuts can be changed by clicking on "
"the button for the action you want to change and then pressing the key you "
"want to use. The changes are loaded by clicking on &nbsp;<guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> or <guibutton>Apply</guibutton>. The current game will be ended "
"and a new one started. You can click on the &nbsp;<guibutton>Defaults</"
"guibutton> button to restore the default Shortcuts."
msgstr ""
"Para escoller o xogador co que queiras xogar, vai á sección Xogador e marca "
"os xogadores. Pódense cambiar os atallos premendo o botón da acción que "
"queiras cambiar e a continuación premendo a tecla que queiras empregar. Os "
"cambios cárganse premendo <guibutton>Aceptar</guibutton> ou "
"<guibutton>Aplicar</guibutton>. A partida actual remata e iníciase unha "
"nova. Pódese premer o botón <guibutton>Predeterminado</guibutton> para "
"restaurar os atallos predeterminados."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a custom Arena"
msgstr "Crear un escenario personalizado"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "An Arena in &granatier; consists of two files, the <filename>myarena."
#| "desktop</filename> and the <filename>myarena.xml</filename>."
msgid ""
"An Arena in &granatier; consists of two files, the <filename>myarena."
"desktop</filename>&nbsp; and the <filename>myarena.xml</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Un escenario de &granatier; consta de dous ficheiros, <filename>myarena."
"desktop</filename> e <filename>myarena.xml</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal role=\"extension\">.desktop</literal> file contains the "
"metadata like the arena name or the author of the arena and consists of the "
"following entries."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[Arena]\n"
"Name=My Arena\n"
"Description=This is my first Arena\n"
"Type=XML\n"
"FileName=myarena.xml\n"
"Author=Joe User\n"
"AuthorEmail=joe.user@foo.org"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can choose whatever name you want, but &nbsp;<literal>FileName</literal> "
"must be the name of the <literal role=\"extension\">.xml</literal> file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <literal role=\"extension\">.xml</literal> file contains the actual "
"arena map."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:396
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The .xml file contains the actual arena map. <programlisting>\n"
#| "&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?&gt;\n"
#| "&lt;Arena arenaFileVersion=\"1\" rowCount=\"13\" colCount=\"17\"&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt; +++++-- --+++++ &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
#| "&lt;/Arena&gt;\n"
#| "      </programlisting> There is no limit for rowCount and colCount, so "
#| "you can choose the size of the arena by yourself. The following symbols "
#| "are used for the arena map."
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;Arena arenaFileVersion=\"1\" rowCount=\"13\" colCount=\"17\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; +++++-- --+++++ &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Arena&gt;"
msgstr ""
"O ficheiro .xml contén o mapa do escenario en si. <programlisting>\n"
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;Arena arenaFileVersion=\"1\" rowCount=\"13\" colCount=\"17\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; +++++-- --+++++ &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;=+++=++_-_++=+++=&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;==++===_-_===++==&lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt; ==+++=_p_=+++== &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  =+++++_+++++=  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;  ===+++++++===  &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"  &lt;Row&gt;    ==== ====    &lt;/Row&gt;\n"
"&lt;/Arena&gt;\n"
"      </programlisting> Non hai límite para rowCount ou colCount, polo que "
"se pode escoller o tamaño do escenario. Os símbolos seguintes empréganse "
"para o mapa do escenario."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is no limit for <literal>rowCount</literal> and <literal>colCount</"
"literal>, so you can choose the size of the arena by yourself. The following "
"symbols are used for the arena map."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"'=' a wall item\n"
"' ' a hole item\n"
"'_' a ground item\n"
"'+' a block item\n"
"'x' will randomly create a block or a ground item\n"
"'-' an ice item\n"
"'o' a mortar item\n"
"'u' an arrow up\n"
"'r' an arrow right\n"
"'d' an arrow down\n"
"'l' an arrow left\n"
"'p' a player position"
msgstr ""
"'=' un elemento de parede\n"
"' ' un elemento de furado\n"
"'_' un elemento de chan\n"
"'+' un elemento de bloque\n"
"'x' crea aleatoriamente un elemento de bloque ou de chan\n"
"'-' un elemento de xeo\n"
"'o' un elemento de morteiro\n"
"'u' unha frecha para riba\n"
"'r' unha frecha para a dereita\n"
"'d' unha frecha para baixo\n"
"'l' unha frecha para a esquerda\n"
"'p' unha posición de xogador"

